abstract: Major Wm. DENMAN, who died on Monday, Sept. 12, in the 76th year of his age, was, at the time of his death, the oldest journalist in the Catholic interest in this country. He was of English birth, and was educated for the military service in Great Britain. At an early ago he retired from army life, and emigrated to this country nearly half a century ago.

abstract: The new Police Commissioners assumed control of the force yesterday afternoon and organized by electing S. M. RANDOLPH Vice-President. The resignations of Chief WILLIAM LEE, all the Captains and several Sargeants and policemen, which bad been tendered, were accepted, and Sergt. BURGESS was elected temporary Chief.
